reviewText:
Early Access Review

Going straight to the point.

Pros

The simulation is extremely real;
The array of equipment is pretty vast;
It is totally free to play;
The graphics and the sounds are really detailed;
Fishing feels very rewarding;
Fine progression;
Really fun, for those who like fishing, to play.

Cons

The game only teaches you how to play with floating rods (there are other equipment which you need to learn by yourself and the game doesn't give you a single tip on what it does or how to use it);
Some items on store need a specific kind of reel and the game doesn't tell you when it is needed;
Frame desynchronization problems;
If you lag, or your connection with the game stops, or if the server stops, there's no message telling you that it happened (when the connection is offline fishes don't come for the bait/lure);
If you run out of virtual money you'll have to buy it with real money;
Some lures can't be attached to certain rods and the game doesn't tell which ones.

In general, the game is damn good, if you like fishing simulators or fishing you MUST play it. Wouldn't suggest spending real money on its beta current state because it feels very defective for a beta test, once things get solved and corrected I think the game will have great value.
